    \"UnityEditor.ShaderGraph.StickyNoteData\",\n    \"m_ObjectId\": \"b67a97ff23d54ecf8c71174270f4822d\",\n   
    \"m_Title\": \"ProPixelizer SubTarget\",\n    \"m_Content\": \"This ShaderGraph
    is using the ProPixelizer SubTarget, which you can select via the Graph Inspector
    -> Graph Settings.\\n\\nThe ProPixelizer SubTarget behaves like a standard 'lit'
    ShaderGraph, but with a lot of extra options! The SubTarget automatically implements
    a number of features for you:\\n- Cel shading using a supplied lighting ramp
    to quantise lighting.\\n- Color grading and dither patterns.\\n- Pixel expansion.\\n-
    Edge, ID and Bevel outlines, which can be controlled per-pixel using the ProPixelizer
    fields on your ShaderGraph output.\\n\\nYou'll also find that the SubTarget will
    automatically add required ProPixelizer properties and keywords to your material.\",\n   
    \"m_TextSize\": 0,\n    \"m_Theme\": 0,\n    \"m_Position\": {\n        \"serializedVersion\":
    \"2\",\n        \"x\": -96.80000305175781,\n        \"y\": 661.5999755859375,\n       
